cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): This paper is about a new Chinese reading comprehension dataset, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and language understanding. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): Machine Reading Comprehension (MRC) is a subfield of AI, and this paper proposes a new dataset for accelerating related research in the community. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The proposed dataset contains large-scale training data, which suggests the use of machine learning techniques for training models on this dataset. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): User query reading comprehension is one of the types of the proposed dataset, which involves retrieving relevant information from a given text. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): Deep learning models are commonly used for MRC tasks, and this paper may involve the use of neural networks for training models on the proposed dataset.
